issue.title: OpenSSL3 branch, failing to build
issue.body:
Hi, 
I was trying to build openssl branch OpenSSL3, with liboqs main branch, but I get the following failures, checked to see the missing symbols are not within liboqs too.

```
gcc  -Iinclude -Iapps/include -I.  -fPIC -pthread -m64 -Wa,--noexecstack -Wall -O3 -DOPENSSL_USE_NODELETE -DL_ENDIAN -DOPENSSL_PIC -DOPENSSLDIR="\"/home/erdem/oqs-openssl3/local\"" -DENGINESDIR="\"/home/erdem/oqs-openssl3/local/lib/engines-3\"" -DMODULESDIR="\"/home/erdem/oqs-openssl3/local/lib/ossl-modules\"" -DOPENSSL_BUILDING_OPENSSL -DNDEBUG  -MMD -MF apps/lib/libtestutil-lib-opt.d.tmp -MT apps/lib/libtestutil-lib-opt.o -c -o apps/lib/libtestutil-lib-opt.o apps/lib/opt.c
providers/implementations/keymgmt/oqs_kmgmt.c: In function 'oqs_sig_default_new_key':
providers/implementations/keymgmt/oqs_kmgmt.c:417:50: error: 'OQS_SIG_alg_default' undeclared (first use in this function); did you mean 'OQS_SIG_alg_count'?
  417 |     return oqsx_key_new(PROV_LIBCTX_OF(provctx), OQS_SIG_alg_default, "oqs_sig_default", 0, NULL);
      |                                                  ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      |                                                  OQS_SIG_alg_count
providers/implementations/keymgmt/oqs_kmgmt.c:417:50: note: each undeclared identifier is reported only once for each function it appears in
gcc  -Iinclude -Iapps/include -I.  -fPIC -pthread -m64 -Wa,--noexecstack -Wall -O3 -DOPENSSL_USE_NODELETE -DL_ENDIAN -DOPENSSL_PIC -DOPENSSLDIR="\"/home/erdem/oqs-openssl3/local\"" -DENGINESDIR="\"/home/erdem/oqs-openssl3/local/lib/engines-3\"" -DMODULESDIR="\"/home/erdem/oqs-openssl3/local/lib/ossl-modules\"" -DOPENSSL_BUILDING_OPENSSL -DNDEBUG  -MMD -MF test/testutil/libtestutil-lib-apps_mem.d.tmp -MT test/testutil/libtestutil-lib-apps_mem.o -c -o test/testutil/libtestutil-lib-apps_mem.o test/testutil/apps_mem.c
providers/implementations/keymgmt/oqs_kmgmt.c: In function 'oqs_sig_default_gen_init':
providers/implementations/keymgmt/oqs_kmgmt.c:422:46: error: 'OQS_SIG_alg_default' undeclared (first use in this function); did you mean 'OQS_SIG_alg_count'?
  422 |     return oqsx_gen_init(provctx, selection, OQS_SIG_alg_default, 0);
      |                                              ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      |                                              OQS_SIG_alg_count
providers/implementations/keymgmt/oqs_kmgmt.c: In function 'dilithium4_new_key':
providers/implementations/keymgmt/oqs_kmgmt.c:445:50: error: 'OQS_SIG_alg_dilithium_4' undeclared (first use in this function); did you mean 'OQS_SIG_alg_dilithium_2'?
  445 |     return oqsx_key_new(PROV_LIBCTX_OF(provctx), OQS_SIG_alg_dilithium_4, "dilithium4", 0, NULL);
      |                                                  ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      |                                                  OQS_SIG_alg_dilithium_2
providers/implementations/keymgmt/oqs_kmgmt.c: In function 'dilithium4_gen_init':
providers/implementations/keymgmt/oqs_kmgmt.c:450:46: error: 'OQS_SIG_alg_dilithium_4' undeclared (first use in this function); did you mean 'OQS_SIG_alg_dilithium_2'?
  450 |     return oqsx_gen_init(provctx, selection, OQS_SIG_alg_dilithium_4, 0);
      |                                              ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      |                                              OQS_SIG_alg_dilithium_2
providers/implementations/keymgmt/oqs_kmgmt.c: In function 'bike1l1cpa_new_key':
providers/implementations/keymgmt/oqs_kmgmt.c:604:50: error: 'OQS_KEM_alg_bike1_l1_cpa' undeclared (first use in this function); did you mean 'OQS_KEM_alg_bike_l1'?
  604 |     return oqsx_key_new(PROV_LIBCTX_OF(provctx), OQS_KEM_alg_bike1_l1_cpa, "bike1l1cpa", 1, NULL);
      |                                                  ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      |                                                  OQS_KEM_alg_bike_l1
gcc  -Iinclude -Iapps/include -I.  -fPIC -pthread -m64 -Wa,--noexecstack -Wall -O3 -DOPENSSL_USE_NODELETE -DL_ENDIAN -DOPENSSL_PIC -DOPENSSLDIR="\"/home/erdem/oqs-openssl3/local\"" -DENGINESDIR="\"/home/erdem/oqs-openssl3/local/lib/engines-3\"" -DMODULESDIR="\"/home/erdem/oqs-openssl3/local/lib/ossl-modules\"" -DOPENSSL_BUILDING_OPENSSL -DNDEBUG  -MMD -MF test/testutil/libtestutil-lib-basic_output.d.tmp -MT test/testutil/libtestutil-lib-basic_output.o -c -o test/testutil/libtestutil-lib-basic_output.o test/testutil/basic_output.c
providers/implementations/keymgmt/oqs_kmgmt.c: In function 'bike1l1cpa_gen_init':
providers/implementations/keymgmt/oqs_kmgmt.c:609:46: error: 'OQS_KEM_alg_bike1_l1_cpa' undeclared (first use in this function); did you mean 'OQS_KEM_alg_bike_l1'?
  609 |     return oqsx_gen_init(provctx, selection, OQS_KEM_alg_bike1_l1_cpa, 1);
      |                                              ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      |                                              OQS_KEM_alg_bike_l1
providers/implementations/signature/oqs_sig.c: In function 'get_oqs_oid':
providers/implementations/signature/oqs_sig.c:81:16: error: 'OQS_SIG_alg_default' undeclared (first use in this function); did you mean 'OQS_SIG_alg_count'?
   81 |    if (!strcmp(OQS_SIG_alg_default, oqs_name))
      |                ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      |                OQS_SIG_alg_count
providers/implementations/signature/oqs_sig.c:81:16: note: each undeclared identifier is reported only once for each function it appears in
providers/implementations/signature/oqs_sig.c:90:16: error: 'OQS_SIG_alg_dilithium_4' undeclared (first use in this function); did you mean 'OQS_SIG_alg_dilithium_2'?
   90 |    if (!strcmp(OQS_SIG_alg_dilithium_4, oqs_name))
      |                ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      |                OQS_SIG_alg_dilithium_2
providers/implementations/signature/oqs_sig.c:122:1: warning: control reaches end of non-void function [-Wreturn-type]
  122 | }
```

Is this a known issue? or did I miss something on my build?
Regards.
